summary:
The Security Council, recalling its previous resolutions on South Sudan, determines that the situation in South Sudan continues to threaten international peace and security. Acting under Article 41 of Chapter VII, it:

1. Renews until 15 April 2016 the measures imposed by paragraphs 9 and 12 of resolution 2206 (2015), reaffirming the provisions of paragraphs 10, 11, 13, 14, and 15;
2. Extends until 15 May 2016 the mandate of the Panel of Experts, with a review of the mandate and potential further extension by 15 April 2016;
3. Remains seized of the matter.
